<item>
            <title>[LU-12516] volatile file creation in .lustre/fid/</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12516</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;this is needed to allow striping manipulation using FID.&lt;br/&gt;
for example, for commands like lfs mirror create /mnt/lustre/.lustre/fid/&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x20000401:0x1:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
this is, in turn, is useful for utilities like automatic file replication which takes FIDs from LiPE and can save on fid2path and subsequent path traversal (number of sync RPCs)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
